ng to address at least aspects of this relationship have appeared in recent years, a principled discussion on how the two disciplines may interact has not yet been carried out in a programmatic way. This volume aims to fill this gap and offers a cross-disciplinary venue for discussing the bridging between sociolinguistic and typological research from various angles, with the ultimate goal of laying out the methodological and conceptual foundations of an integrated research agenda for the study of linguistic variation.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aSoziolinguistik. 4aSprachtypologie. 4aSprachvariation.  aLanguage Variation.  aLinguistic Typology.  aSociolinguistics.1 aBallarè, Silvia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBallarè, Silvia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBarotto, Alessandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCornillie, Bert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerrarotti, Lorenzo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuzmán Naranjo, Matías, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHasse, Anja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInglese, Guglielmo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInglese, Guglielmo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMattiola, Simone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMauri, Caterina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOchs, Samira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosemeyer, Malte, econtribut